The paper deals with the design of families of complex valued sequences with low correlation properties, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiplicative and additive characters of finite fields suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and number theory (cs.NA). The efficient implementation of the sequences also suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
